ibrary update target** | The metadata and test directories selected for a `library-update-request` coordinate (§WF-improve-library-coverage.3). Resolution records the requested coordinate, match type (`tested-version`, `metadata-version`, `default-for`, or `new-version`), matched index entry, resolved metadata version, resolved test version, and edit directories. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:142:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:143:  workflows (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:170:  If the current dynamic-access report has more uncovered classes than this\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:178:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:206:  `improve-coverage-…`, `fix-javac-…`, `fix-java-run-…`,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:215:coverage, and status evidence stays attached to the library version it describes\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:216:(§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage). During a run, in-flight metrics are staged\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:335:- Dynamic-access coverage remains missing or suspiciously low after a\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:340:- Publication detects a severe metadata, test, or coverage anomaly that makes\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:441:| `RUN_STATUS_CHUNK_READY` | A chunked dynamic-access run reached a reviewable class boundary and §FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification passed for the current part. The current part is PR-eligible, and the issue must not be resumed until the part PR has merged. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:449:must run or refresh the dynamic-access report before choosing the execution\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:450:mode. If the current report has more uncovered dynamic-access classes than the\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:459:`chunked-dynamic-access` label. The normal project status remains the run-state\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:465:by §WF-dynami