flow is returned unchanged and the dynamic-access coverage phase is\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:73:dynamic-access phase, using the same strategy bundle's dynamic-access prompt\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:75:directly with the iterative dynamic-access phase.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:79:iterative phase refines remaining call sites; and library-update coverage\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:80:strategies, where Forge improves dynamic-access coverage on existing tests\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:83:### WF-dynamic-access-fallback-and-failure: Required fallback and failure behavior\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:87:dynamic-access report cannot provide guidance: the Gradle report task fails,\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:88:the report file is missing or unparsable, dynamic-access reporting is disabled,\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:89:or the report has zero dynamic-access calls. Once a dynamic-access phase has\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:96:2. The dynamic-access report disappears or becomes unreadable after the\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:97:   workflow has started using dynamic-access guidance.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:99:   `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` was not requested.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:108:dynamic-access coverage phase.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:112:Every dynamic-access run shares a small set of inputs; the rest are supplied by\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:123:| Strategy bundle | `--strategy-name <name>`, selecting one dynamic-access bundle |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:131:the class prompt template (`prompts[\"dynamic-access-iteration\"]`, see §6.2),\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:133:default 5, must be `>= 1`). `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` is honored\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:140:template (`prompts[\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\"]`).\n